result.execSummary:
The defendant Chad Michael Ernzen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Chad Michael Ernzen is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Chad Michael Ernzen was found guilty of Homicide by Veh. Use-Control. Substance, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.09(1)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 2:30. Defendant Chad Michael Ernzen in court, in custody with attorney Guy Mason Taylor.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Taylor informs the Court matters are resolved.  Joint recommendation.  Defendant changes his plea from Not Guilty to Guilty on Count 1.  Attorney Taylor files Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form, and Plea Agreement with the Court.  The Court questions Defendant regarding his plea change and the plea questionnaire and waiver of rights form.  Court questions Attorney Taylor regarding Defendant's plea change and the plea questionnaire and waiver of rights form.  Parties stipulate to factual basis.  State waives the right to Jury Trial.  Court is satisfied Defendant enters his plea freely, knowingly, voluntarily, and intelligently, adjudicating Defendant Guilty.  Attorney Taylor requesting moving forward with sentencing today.  State moves to dismiss Count 2 in this case, Counts 1 and 2 in case 17-CF-02, and Count 1 in case 16-CF-74.  Court will order.  Court orders a Pre-Sentence Investigation in this matter.
